{
  "texts": [
    "FunctionAlgorithm 3:3SortAscendingByValueOnFrequency(LSG, sb): sortedSenList:= SortAscendingByValueOnFrequency(LSG, sb)// Sort the Linearized group for switchboard state on frequency of repeated sensor values as in Fig. 11. return sortedSenList return Function Total(sortedSenList): T: = ∑ end i=1 sortedSenList f i return T return Function FindPrLeft(index, sortedSenList, T): n:= index PrLeft: = ∑ n-1 i=1 sortedSenList f i /T return PrLeft return Function FindPrRight(index, sortedSenList, T): n:= index end:= lastIndex(sortedSenList) PrRight: = ∑ end i=n+1 sortedSenList f i /T return PrRight return Function FindAnomPr(PrLe f t, PrRight): if PrLeft ==0 or PrRight ==0 then PrAnom: = 1// flag anomaly end else if PrLeft̸ = 0.5 and PrRight̸ = 0.5 then PrAnom:= |0.5-min(PrLeft, PrRight)| •2 end else PrAnom:= 0.5 end if PrLeft + PrRight <0.5 then PrAnom: = |PrLeft+PrRight| end if PrRight == 0 and PrLeft ̸ =1 then PrAnom: = PrLeft end else if PrLeft == 0 and PrRight̸ = 1 then PrAnom: = PrRight end return index, 1-PrAnom// Not anomaly probability return Function FindSWProduct(index, swlen, LSG, sb): sortedSenList:= SortAscendingByValueOnFrequency(LSG, sb) T:= Total(sortedSenList) PrLeft:= FindPrLeft(index, sortedSenList, T) PrRight:= FindPrRight(index, sortedSenList, T) PrAnom:= FindAnomPr(PrLe f t, PrRight) swproduct:= ∏ Index i=Index-swlen+1 (1 -PrAnom i) return swproduct return Function FindMinMaxProduct(index, swlen, LSG, sb): // swlen 5, 10, 25, 50, 100 are used end:= lastIndex(LSG, sb) minswprod:= inf// A large positive number maxswprod:=inf// A large negative number for i=1 to end do swprod:= FindSWProduct(index, swlen, LSG, sb) minswprod:= min(minswprod, swprod) maxswprod:= max(maxswprod, swprod) end return minswprod, maxswprod// Do for each sb state return Extended Detection Training Functions example see Fig.",
    "Table 1:1The sensors and actuators in each process stage[12].ProcessSensorActuatorP1LIT-101, FIT-101MV-101, P101P2AIT-201, AIT-202, AIT-203, FIT-201MV-201, P-201, P-202, P-203, P-204, P-205, P-206P3DPIT-301, FIT-301, LIT-301MV-301, MV-302, MV-303, MV-304, P-301, P-302P4AIT-401, AIT-402, FIT-401, LIT-401P-401, P-402, P-403, P-404, UV-401AIT-501, AIT-502, AIT-503, AIT-504,P5FIT-501, FIT-502, FIT-503, FIT-504,P-501, P-502PIT-501, PIT-502, PIT-503P6FIT-601P-601, P-602, P-603The SWaT datasets provided the state view of the fifty-onesensors and actuators in the plant at one second resolution, as timeseries data.",
